#!CNavyBlue #!N  #!Rcamsec Camera Class #!N #!EC #!N #!N 
A Camera Object stores parameters that relate a scene to an 
image of the scene, including camera position and orientation, field of 
view, type of projection, and resolution. It specifies the transformation from 
world coordinates to image coordinates. #!N #!I0 #!N #!N #!I0 #!N 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*    #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Camera DXNewCamera() #!EF #!EF #!I50 #!N Creates a new 
Camera. See  #!Ldxnca,dxall1311 h DXNewCamera  #!EL  . #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*    #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Camera DXSetView() 
#!EF #!EF #!I50 #!N Specifies the Camera position, a point on 
the line of sight of the Camera, and the Camera orientation. 
See  #!Ldxsvw,dxall1393 h DXSetView, DXGetView  #!EL  . #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*    #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Camera DXSetOrthographic() #!EF 
#!EF #!I50 #!N Specifies an orthographic view. The width of the 
viewport in the world coordinates and the aspect ratio are specified. 
See  #!Ldxsoc,dxall1384 h DXSetOrthographic, DXGetOrthographic  #!EL  . #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*    #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Camera DXSetPerspective() #!EF 
#!EF #!I50 #!N Specifies a perspective view. The field of view 
specifies the tangent of half the angle of the field of 
view. The height of the view is the specified  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   aspect 
#!EF times the width. See  #!Ldxspe,dxall1388 h DXSetPerspective, DXGetPerspective  #!EL  . #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
